{
    "title": "Technology as Medium, Not Message",
    "description": "Understanding that the same technology can serve different purposes—entertainment or transformation",
    "theme": {
        "primaryColor": "#5900ff",
        "fontBody": "Rajdhani, sans-serif"
    },
    "modules": [
        {
            "id": "auditor_workflow_1.3",
            "title": "Experience Audit",
            "type": "scenario-based",
            "content": {
                "scenes": [
                    {
                        "id": "intro",
                        "narrative": "<h3>System Initialized</h3><p>Welcome, <strong>Digital Auditor</strong>. Your task is to evaluate three VR prototypes and determine their category. Is the technology serving as a <strong>Cyberdelic Medium</strong>, or is it <strong>Pure Entertainment</strong>?</p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "start_audit",
                                "label": "Begin Audit",
                                "outcome": "exp1"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp1",
                        "narrative": "<h3>Experience 1: Virtual Temple</h3><p>Users sit in a virtual temple with guided breathwork and biofeedback-driven lighting. The technology fades into the background as attention turns inward.</p><p><strong>Categorization?</strong></p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "exp1_c",
                                "label": "Cyberdelic",
                                "outcome": "exp1_correct"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "exp1_e",
                                "label": "Entertainment/Social",
                                "outcome": "exp1_wrong"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp1_correct",
                        "narrative": "<h3>✓ Validated</h3><p>Correct. It uses technology to facilitate altered states and transformation. The gear serves the inward journey.</p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "next",
                                "label": "Review Next Prototype",
                                "outcome": "exp2"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp1_wrong",
                        "narrative": "<h3>Inaccurate</h3><p>This experience has all three cyberdelic components: digital tech, altered states, and transformational intent. It's not just a game.</p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "retry",
                                "label": "Re-evaluate",
                                "outcome": "exp1"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp2",
                        "narrative": "<h3>Experience 2: VR Roller Coaster</h3><p>High-speed drops and adrenaline. Biofeedback monitors heart rate merely to display an 'Excitement Score'. Immersion is purely external engagement.</p><p><strong>Categorization?</strong></p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "exp2_c",
                                "label": "Cyberdelic",
                                "outcome": "exp2_wrong"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "exp2_e",
                                "label": "Entertainment",
                                "outcome": "exp2_correct"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp2_correct",
                        "narrative": "<h3>✓ Validated</h3><p>Correct. Despite the high-end tech, the purpose is outward engagement and thrills, not inner exploration. Same tools, different purpose.</p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "next",
                                "label": "Review Final Prototype",
                                "outcome": "exp3"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp2_wrong",
                        "narrative": "<h3>Inaccurate</h3><p>Simply having a VR headset and heart sensors doesn't make it cyberdelic. Without transformational intent, it's just a thrill ride.</p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "retry",
                                "label": "Re-evaluate",
                                "outcome": "exp2"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp3",
                        "narrative": "<h3>Experience 3: Social VR Hanging</h3><p>A platform for chatting and casual games. It creates meaningful presence and connection across distance, focused on social entertainment.</p><p><strong>Categorization?</strong></p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "exp3_c",
                                "label": "Cyberdelic",
                                "outcome": "exp3_wrong"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "exp3_e",
                                "label": "Social VR",
                                "outcome": "exp3_correct"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp3_correct",
                        "narrative": "<h3>✓ Validated</h3><p>Correct. While connection is valuable, the intent is social interaction, not the cultivation of consciousness-exploring altered states.</p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "finish",
                                "label": "Review Audit Results",
                                "outcome": "flow_next_module"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "exp3_wrong",
                        "narrative": "<h3>Inaccurate</h3><p>Connection and presence are vital, but this platform lacks the specific cultivation of altered states meant for transformation.</p>",
                        "choices": [
                            {
                                "id": "retry",
                                "label": "Re-evaluate",
                                "outcome": "exp3"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "medium_message_logic_1.3",
            "title": "The Audit Logic",
            "type": "scenario-based",
            "scenes": [
                {
                    "id": "reveal",
                    "narrative": "<h3>The McLuhan Reversal</h3><p>You've evaluated three experiences using identical hardware. This reveals our core principle: <strong>The hardware is neutral.</strong></p><p>In most tech, 'the medium is the message.' In cyberdelics, this is reversed: <strong>Consciousness exploration is the message; technology is merely the medium.</strong></p>",
                    "choices": [
                        {
                            "id": "continue",
                            "label": "Apply This Logic",
                            "outcome": "test_logic"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "test_logic",
                    "narrative": "<h3>Final Audit Check</h3><p>A developer wants to create a new cyberdelic module. What should be their <strong>primary</strong> design priority?</p>",
                    "choices": [
                        {
                            "id": "tech",
                            "label": "Highest resolution graphics and fastest tracking possible",
                            "outcome": "tech_wrong"
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "intent",
                            "label": "Facilitating inward exploration and consciousness shifts",
                            "outcome": "intent_correct"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "tech_wrong",
                    "narrative": "<h3>Instructional Error</h3><p>High-end specs are useful, but they don't define the category. Some of the most effective tools use minimal visuals. Intent must come first.</p>",
                    "choices": [
                        {
                            "id": "retry",
                            "label": "Try Again",
                            "outcome": "test_logic"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "intent_correct",
                    "narrative": "<h3>Logic Verified</h3><p>Exactly. The purpose—facultative consciousness exploration—defines how the tool is built. Hardware serves the intent.</p>",
                    "choices": [
                        {
                            "id": "finish",
                            "label": "Complete Lesson",
                            "outcome": "flow_next_module"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}